echo "                </button>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"modalContentBundleAll\" style=\"display: none\">\n    <span class=\"modal-header\" style=\"display: none\">Bundle Sitejet Builder with Existing Hosting Plans</span>\n\n    <p>To offer Sitejet Builder in your cPanel & WHM or Plesk hosting plans, you must grant the necessary features and required permissions. The easiest way to do this is updating the feature lists and service plans that your hosting plans already use.</p>\n\n    <ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\" role=\"tablist\">\n        <li role=\"presentation\" class=\"active\"><a href=\"#bundleAllCpanel\" aria-controls=\"bundleAllCpanel\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">cPanel & WHM</a></li>\n        <li role=\"presentation\"><a href=\"#bundleAllPlesk\" aria-controls=\"bundleAllPlesk\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Plesk</a></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"bundleAllCpanel\">\n            <p>To configure Sitejet Builder for cPanel & WHM hosting plans:</p>\n\n            <ol>\n                <li>Log in to WHM.</li>\n                <li>Go to <strong>Home » Packages » Feature Manager</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Under <strong>Manage feature list</strong>, select the feature list that you use for your WHMCS hosting packages and click <strong>Edit</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Make certain that <em>Sitejet Builder</em> is selected in the list of features.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n                <li>If you use more than one feature list for your WHMCS hosting packages, repeat these steps for each feature list that you use.</li>\n            </ol>\n\n            <p>Perform these steps on every cPanel & WHM server that hosts accounts for which you want to offer Sitejet Builder.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"bundleAllPlesk\">\n            <p>To configure Sitejet Builder for Plesk hosting plans:</p>\n\n            <ol>\n                <li>Log in to Plesk.</li>\n                <li>Go to <strong>Service Plans</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Edit the service plan that you use for your WHMCS hosting packages.</li>\n                <li>Under <strong>Permissions</strong>, select <em>Access to Sitejet Builder</em>.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n                <li>If you use more than one service plan for your WHMCS hosting packages, repeat these steps for each service plan that you use.</li>\n            </ol>\n\n            <p>Perform these steps on every Plesk server that hosts accounts for which you want to offer Sitejet Builder.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <p>When you have finished updating your feature lists and service plans, go back to WHMCS and verify your changes at <strong>Configuration (<i class=\"fa fa-wrench\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>) > System Settings > Products/Services</strong>. <em>Sitejet Included</em> will display in the <strong>Features</strong> column for products that include Sitejet Builder. You may need to click <strong>Refresh Feature Status</strong> to see the effects of your changes.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n<div id=\"modalContentBundleSelected\" style=\"display: none\">\n    <span class=\"modal-header\" style=\"display: none\">Bundle Sitejet Builder with Selected Hosting Plans</span>\n\n    <p>To offer Sitejet Builder in your cPanel & WHM or Plesk hosting plans, you must grant the necessary features and required permissions. If you do not want to offer Sitejet Builder on every hosting plan that uses a given feature list or service plan, you can create new feature lists and service plans for offering Sitejet Builder.</p>\n\n    <ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\" role=\"tablist\">\n        <li role=\"presentation\" class=\"active\"><a href=\"#bundleSelectCpanel\" aria-controls=\"bundleSelectCpanel\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">cPanel & WHM</a></li>\n        <li role=\"presentation\"><a href=\"#bundleSelectPlesk\" aria-controls=\"bundleSelectPlesk\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Plesk</a></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"bundleSelectCpanel\">\n            <p>To add a new feature list that includes Sitejet Builder and configure your packages for cPanel & WHM hosting plans:</p>\n\n            <ol>\n                <li>Log in to WHM.</li>\n                <li>Go to <strong>Home » Packages » Feature Manager</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Under <strong>Add a new feature list</strong>, enter the new feature list's name and click <strong>Add Feature List</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Choose the features that you want to include, making sure to select <em>Sitejet Builder</em>.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Go to <strong>Home » Packages » Edit a Package</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Select the package that you want to configure to use the new feature list.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Select the new feature list for <strong>Feature List</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Continue editing additional packages until all of the packages that will include Sitejet Builder use the new feature list.</li>\n            </ol>\n\n            <p>You may wish to also check your existing feature lists to ensure that Sitejet Builder is not selected for feature lists or packages that should not include it.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"bundleSelectPlesk\">\n            <p>To enable access for a new Plesk hosting plan, you must assign the appropriate permission to a new service plan.</p>\n            <ol>\n                <li>Log in to Plesk.</li>\n                <li>Go to <strong>Service Plans</strong> and click <strong>Add a Plan</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Create your new plan, making sure to select <em>Access to Sitejet Builder</em> under <strong>Permissions</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Repeat these steps to create any additional plans that include Sitejet Builder.</li>\n            </ol>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <p>When you have finished creating feature lists and updating hosting packages and service plans, go back to WHMCS and verify your changes at <strong>Configuration (<i class=\"fa fa-wrench\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>) > System Settings > Products/Services</strong>. <em>Sitejet Included</em> will display in the <strong>Features</strong> column for products that include Sitejet Builder. You may need to click <strong>Refresh Feature Status</strong> to see the effects of your changes.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"modalContentAddon\" style=\"display: none\">\n    <span class=\"modal-header\" style=\"display: none\">Offer Sitejet Builder as a Product Addon</span>\n\n    <p>Product addons allow your customers to select optional additions, like Sitejet Builder, to the products that they purchase from you.</p>\n    <p>To create a product addon for Sitejet Builder:</p>\n\n    <ol>\n        <li>Go to <strong>(<i class=\"fa fa-wrench\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>) > System Settings > Product Addons</strong>.</li>\n        <li>Click <strong>Add New Addon</strong>.</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <ul class=\"nav nav-tabs\" role=\"tablist\">\n        <li role=\"presentation\" class=\"active\"><a href=\"#bundleAddonAutomatic\" aria-controls=\"bundleAddonAutomatic\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Predefined Sitejet Builder Addon</a></li>\n        <li role=\"presentation\"><a href=\"#bundleAddonManual\" aria-controls=\"bundleAddonManual\" role=\"tab\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Custom Sitejet Builder Addon</a></li>\n    </ul>\n    <div class=\"tab-content\">\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane active\" id=\"bundleAddonAutomatic\">\n            <p>Click the appropriate option under <strong>Predefined Addons</strong>: <em>Sitejet Builder for cPanel & WHM</em> or <em>Sitejet Builder for Plesk</em>.</p>\n        </div>\n        <div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"bundleAddonManual\">\n            <ol>\n                <li>Under <strong>Addon Type</strong>, select <em>Add-On Feature</em>.</li>\n                <li>Enter the desired addon display name.</li>\n                <li>For <strong>Module</strong>, choose the server type (<em>cPanel</em> or <em>Plesk</em>).</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Continue</strong>.</li>\n                <li>Choose the <strong>Module Settings</strong> tab.</li>\n                <li>For <strong>Feature Name</strong>, select <em>Sitejet Builder</em>.</li>\n                <li>For <strong>Automation Settings</strong>, select <em>Automatically set up the addon as soon as the first payment is received</em>. This causes automatic provisioning to occur on payment.</li>\n                <li>Choose the <strong>Applicable Products</strong> tab.</li>\n                <li>Select the products for which the Sitejet Builder product addon will be available.</li>\n                <li>Configure the remaining product addon settings as desired.</li>\n                <li>Click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</li>\n            </ol>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n\n<script>\n    jQuery(document).ready(function() {\n        jQuery('button[data-open-modal]').click(function() {\n            const button = this;\n            const modalDialog = jQuery('#modalSitejetOffer');\n\n            const modalContent = jQuery((jQuery(button).data('open-modal')));\n\n            modalDialog.find('.modal-title').text(modalContent.find('.modal-header').text());\n            modalDialog.find('.modal-body').html(modalContent.html());\n\n            modalDialog.find('a.btn-learn-more').attr(\n                'href',\n                modalContent.find('a.learn-more-link').attr('href')\n    